**Title:** COM – RFID/NFC Community – SAINTCON

**URL:** [https://saintcon.org/com-rfid-nfc-community/](https://saintcon.org/com-rfid-nfc-community/)

**Description:** 
Brought to you by Iceman and Gobo42. RFID/NFC can be a difficult technology to understand. Come learn how! We can help you discover how short range wireless communication through RFID works, and how you can take advantage of it, or secure it. We can help you explore the various tools and techniques that can be used to read/store/replay/sniff/scan/bru.

**Community Offerings:**
- Hands-on experience with RFID/NFC technology.
- A Capture The Flag (CTF) event that starts from zero knowledge to advanced usage.
- Tools introduced include:
  - Proxmark3
  - Chameleon Ultra
  - Flipper Zero

**What to Bring:**
- A Laptop
- RFID cards for investigation
- RFID reading devices (Proxmark3/Chameleon Ultra/Flipper Zero)

**Hours of Operation:**
- Monday: Expo Closed
- Tuesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- Wednesday: 10:30 AM – 5:00 PM
- Thursday: 9:00 AM – 5:00 PM
- Friday: 9:00 AM – 11:00 AM

**What You Will Learn:**
- Functionality of RFID/NFC Technology.
- How to read basic NFC Tags.
- Use of the FlipperZero in RFID/NFC attacks.
- Understanding and evaluating system vulnerabilities.

**MiniBadge:**
Details about a MiniBadge that will be available at the Community booth for collection.

**Desktop Wallpaper:**
Community desktop wallpaper is available for download.